00:25:57,222 --> 00:25:58,348
The world must look rosy to her.

278
00:25:58,431 --> 00:25:59,391
You would think so, right?

279
00:25:59,474 --> 00:26:01,726
But her donor was a man
who always stood by her side,

280
00:26:01,810 --> 00:26:04,479
and someone
that she always treated harshly.

281
00:26:06,147 --> 00:26:08,900
In that case, how would you feel
as a human?

282
00:26:09,901 --> 00:26:11,027
As a human?

283
00:26:14,948 --> 00:26:16,616
Even so, wouldn't you still be grateful?

284
00:26:17,701 --> 00:26:19,786
-Why?
-It'll drive you crazy.

285
00:26:19,869 --> 00:26:21,746
Humans can go crazy.

286
00:26:21,830 --> 00:26:24,541
I thought about it,
and that must be why she smiled like that.

287
00:26:24,624 --> 00:26:26,251
No. No way.

288
00:26:26,334 --> 00:26:27,836
She's emotionally unavailable.

289
00:26:27,919 --> 00:26:30,005
She's emotionally unavailable
that I can't get her to love.

290
00:26:30,422 --> 00:26:31,881
I can't. Impossible. I can't do this.

291
00:26:31,965 --> 00:26:33,800
Then you should give up now

292
00:26:33,883 --> 00:26:35,010
and turn to dust.

293
00:26:36,428 --> 00:26:38,555
Why does it have to be her? Why?

294
00:26:38,638 --> 00:26:40,682
Why did you have to save her, then?

295
00:26:40,765 --> 00:26:41,808
That's because...

296
00:26:51,526 --> 00:26:52,736
Lastly,

297
00:26:53,945 --> 00:26:55,322
shine brightly.

298
00:26:56,906 --> 00:26:57,907
What?

299
00:27:01,786 --> 00:27:02,829
What is this?

300
00:27:04,581 --> 00:27:05,415
Hey, Hu.

301
00:27:07,375 --> 00:27:08,251
Hu.

302
00:27:08,793 --> 00:27:09,627
Hu?

303
00:27:25,018 --> 00:27:26,061
Ms. Lee.

304
00:27:27,395 --> 00:27:28,438
Ms. Lee.

305
00:27:34,736 --> 00:27:36,237
We said our last goodbyes to Mr. Cho

306
00:27:36,988 --> 00:27:37,906
earlier this morning.

307
00:27:39,824 --> 00:27:40,700
What?

308
00:27:41,993 --> 00:27:43,828
Were you doing this all night long?

309
00:27:44,829 --> 00:27:45,747
Yes.

310
00:27:48,666 --> 00:27:49,834
What about your eye drops?

311
00:27:50,418 --> 00:27:51,586
Did you put them in?

312
00:27:52,379 --> 00:27:53,588
Of course, you didn't.

313
00:27:53,797 --> 00:27:55,048
Because I had it.

314
00:27:58,051 --> 00:27:59,427
What are you doing?

315
00:27:59,594 --> 00:28:01,262
No, what are you doing?

316
00:28:03,765 --> 00:28:06,393
Those are Mr. Cho's eyes.

317
00:28:07,477 --> 00:28:08,853
I don't care if you starve, get sick,

318
00:28:08,937 --> 00:28:10,230
get sleep, or don't get any sleep.

319
00:28:10,313 --> 00:28:11,481
That's up to you.

320
00:28:11,689 --> 00:28:12,816
But not your eyes.

321
00:28:12,982 --> 00:28:14,484
You got them from Mr. Cho.

322
00:28:16,945 --> 00:28:18,321
I never asked him for them.

323
00:28:18,405 --> 00:28:19,989
Then you can take them back out.

324
00:28:28,957 --> 00:28:31,084
What I am trying to say
is that there is no one who will

325
00:28:31,376 --> 00:28:32,585
take your whining anymore.

326
00:28:33,545 --> 00:28:34,712
You probably don't know,

327
00:28:34,796 --> 00:28:37,090
but Mr. Cho was special to all of us.

328
00:28:37,465 --> 00:28:38,883
Not only did he celebrate our birthdays,

329
00:28:38,967 --> 00:28:40,468
he even celebrated
our families' birthdays.

330
00:28:41,428 --> 00:28:42,929
If you got the eyes from someone like him,

331
00:28:43,012 --> 00:28:44,472
then don't let them go to waste.

332
00:28:44,723 --> 00:28:45,807
I ask of you.

333
00:28:46,057 --> 00:28:47,058
If you liked him that much,

334
00:28:47,142 --> 00:28:48,935
why didn't you treat him
better when he was here?

335
00:28:50,770 --> 00:28:53,064
You slacked off because Mr. Cho was here.

336
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:55,525
All the other employees made Mr. Cho do

337
00:28:55,608 --> 00:28:57,068
all the tough and tedious work.

338
00:28:58,069 --> 00:28:59,446
And now you're getting angry?

339
00:29:05,577 --> 00:29:06,494
Thanks for the speech.

340
00:29:09,414 --> 00:29:11,291
That really resonated in my heart.

341
00:29:13,793 --> 00:29:14,878
Have you forgotten?

342
00:29:15,336 --> 00:29:17,797
His tough and tedious work was you.

343
00:29:19,549 --> 00:29:21,050
Fine, you can mock me all you want.

344
00:29:21,134 --> 00:29:23,094
That suits you the best.

345
00:29:38,693 --> 00:29:39,694
What's wrong?

346
00:29:44,657 --> 00:29:45,742
I can't go.

347
00:29:50,747 --> 00:29:52,081
I know this place.

348
00:29:53,917 --> 00:29:55,543
I can see everything.

349
00:29:56,753 --> 00:29:58,004
But my legs...

350
00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:01,132
My legs won't move.

351
00:30:07,138 --> 00:30:08,515
A psychological trauma?

352
00:30:08,598 --> 00:30:10,517
People usually suffer from this
when they lose someone

353
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:11,684
who was the closest to them.

354
00:30:12,018 --> 00:30:13,645
They cannot do anything

355
00:30:13,728 --> 00:30:14,979
that they did with that person.

356
00:30:15,063 --> 00:30:17,524
A husband that lost his wife

357
00:30:17,607 --> 00:30:19,067
who played bowling with him every Sunday,

358
00:30:19,150 --> 00:30:21,402
has dry heaves whenever
he sees bowling pins,

359
00:30:21,486 --> 00:30:23,154
and even has panic attacks.

360
00:30:23,822 --> 00:30:26,658
The closer they are,
the more severe the symptom is.

361
00:30:27,116 --> 00:30:28,701
You should get hospitalized again.

362
00:30:29,077 --> 00:30:30,829
It only has been a few days
since the accident.

363
00:30:30,912 --> 00:30:33,414
You can see things when you become weak.

364
00:30:33,498 --> 00:30:35,208
I talked to her doctor.

365
00:30:35,500 --> 00:30:37,126
Her inflammation level and leukocyte count

366
00:30:37,210 --> 00:30:38,545
all look normal.

367
00:30:38,795 --> 00:30:40,630
She can get discharged and rest at home

368
00:30:40,713 --> 00:30:42,215
to fully recover soon.

369
00:30:42,882 --> 00:30:44,217
So my heart is the problem?

370
00:30:46,803 --> 00:30:48,721
I can't do the things

371
00:30:50,098 --> 00:30:51,391
that I did with him?

372
00:30:54,018 --> 00:30:54,978
I

373
00:30:55,436 --> 00:30:57,730
did everything with him.

374
00:30:57,814 --> 00:30:59,649
I walked, ran, and ate with him.

375
00:30:59,941 --> 00:31:00,984
Everything.

376
00:31:03,570 --> 00:31:04,654
And I can't do

377
00:31:06,072 --> 00:31:07,532
any of that now?

378
00:31:08,283 --> 00:31:09,284
Although...

379
00:31:11,119 --> 00:31:12,704
Although I can see now?

380
00:31:38,146 --> 00:31:39,147
Too fast.

381
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:43,234
Who are you?

382
00:31:43,484 --> 00:31:44,903
You're 16th note faster.

383
00:31:45,236 --> 00:31:47,363
If you die, get sad,

384
00:31:47,447 --> 00:31:49,324
and fall in love before the music,

385
00:31:49,908 --> 00:31:51,618
it's rushed and kills the expectations.

386
00:31:51,701 --> 00:31:52,952
I asked you who you are.

387
00:31:53,494 --> 00:31:54,495
Corps de ballet.

388
00:31:55,538 --> 00:31:56,581
Your backs aren't straight.

389
00:31:56,664 --> 00:31:58,499
You need to get tensed up!

390
00:31:58,791 --> 00:32:01,169
Dancers express their emotions
with their backs.

391
00:32:01,252 --> 00:32:02,170
Isn't this basic?

392
00:32:02,587 --> 00:32:03,671
One dancer with loose muscles

393
00:32:03,755 --> 00:32:05,757
is enough to ruin the whole
atmosphere of the performance.

394
00:32:07,175 --> 00:32:09,260
-Do you not know that?
-Hey, hey.

395
00:32:12,889 --> 00:32:14,182
Swan Lake.

396
00:32:16,851 --> 00:32:18,227
A happy ending?

397
00:32:18,603 --> 00:32:21,397
Is this intended for kids?

398
00:32:23,191 --> 00:32:24,525
I apologize for my late introduction.

399
00:32:24,734 --> 00:32:26,444
I'm a newly appointed artistic director.

400
00:32:26,527 --> 00:32:27,779
My name is Ji Kang-woo.

401
00:32:29,238 --> 00:32:30,490
Director Ji Kang-woo.

402
00:32:33,201 --> 00:32:34,661
I'm Keum Ru-na, the Associate Director.

403
00:32:35,828 --> 00:32:38,623
Assemble everyone within 30 minutes.

404
00:32:39,374 --> 00:32:42,085
Aren't you tired of doing
the same performance for three years?

405
00:32:42,168 --> 00:32:43,378
Your program is stuck in a rut.

406
00:32:43,461 --> 00:32:46,005
You only perform these predictable shows
for the sake of your popularity.

407
00:32:46,255 --> 00:32:49,092
Can you call yourself
the best ballet company?

408
00:32:49,425 --> 00:32:51,469
Have you watched our show in person?

409
00:32:52,762 --> 00:32:55,306
Our dance and music might not be

410
00:32:55,390 --> 00:32:56,808
perfectly synced in a video.

411
00:32:56,891 --> 00:33:00,061
We all do our best on stage.

412
00:33:00,269 --> 00:33:02,105
If that's your best, you're in trouble.

413
00:33:02,939 --> 00:33:04,482
I saw your show in person
with my own eyes.

414
00:33:05,525 --> 00:33:07,235
The performance for the 20th anniversary.

415
00:33:13,658 --> 00:33:15,368
You must practice more, Ni-na.

416
00:33:15,660 --> 00:33:17,203
Even if you split
the music into 32nd notes,

417
00:33:17,286 --> 00:33:18,705
instead of 16th notes,

418
00:33:18,788 --> 00:33:20,289
I'm confident that I'll stay on the beat.

419
00:33:20,373 --> 00:33:21,457
You're ahead of the music.

420
00:33:22,667 --> 00:33:24,460
I'm sure the critics who are sponsored

421
00:33:24,544 --> 00:33:25,878
by Fantasia never mentioned that.

422
00:33:25,962 --> 00:33:27,130
You should check it now.

423
00:33:27,213 --> 00:33:28,214
Next time.

424
00:33:28,548 --> 00:33:31,259
Right now,
I'm discussing the future of Fantasia.

425
00:33:31,592 --> 00:33:33,052
-Play the music.
-This year,

426
00:33:33,845 --> 00:33:35,555
we won't be performing Swan Lake.

427
00:33:36,014 --> 00:33:38,307
-What?
-We're not doing that?

428
00:33:39,308 --> 00:33:40,768
-Seriously?
-But we practiced.

429
00:33:40,935 --> 00:33:43,730
We've already released
the schedule for the year.

430
00:33:43,855 --> 00:33:45,690
We will do a new show
on the scheduled dates.

431
00:33:45,773 --> 00:33:48,901
Artistic merits, popularity, tradition,
and originality. We'll cover it all.

432
00:33:48,985 --> 00:33:51,821
This will be a new kind of Giselle
no one has ever seen before.

433
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:53,031
-Giselle?
-Giselle?

434
00:33:53,322 --> 00:33:55,950
And the main ballerina for the performance

435
00:33:58,619 --> 00:34:00,413
is Lee Yeon-seo.

436
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:08,379
Who gave you the right
to change the program

437
00:34:08,629 --> 00:34:11,424
and to select the main ballerina?

438
00:34:11,758 --> 00:34:13,676
This is my turf.

439
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:15,386
And only one dancer
will be the main ballerina.

440
00:34:15,470 --> 00:34:16,971
And that dancer is Keum Ni-na.

441
00:34:17,722 --> 00:34:20,558
Everyone, why are you just standing there?

442
00:34:20,641 --> 00:34:21,851
You should go and practice.

443
00:34:22,935 --> 00:34:24,020
Come with me.

444
00:34:26,522 --> 00:34:27,857
Come with me.

445
00:34:28,816 --> 00:34:30,693
I told you to come with me!

446
00:34:30,777 --> 00:34:32,779
You must practice! You must!

447
00:34:33,488 --> 00:34:34,530
Hey, Keum Ni-na.

448
00:34:34,614 --> 00:34:36,407
Shouldn't you at least follow me?

449
00:34:36,491 --> 00:34:37,492
I raised you.

450
00:34:48,836 --> 00:34:50,797
What a bold introduction!

451
00:34:53,007 --> 00:34:54,675
You should have given me a heads-up.

452
00:34:55,676 --> 00:34:56,803
I was very surprised.

453
00:35:01,599 --> 00:35:02,850
Let me introduce him officially.

454
00:35:02,934 --> 00:35:06,020
He will join Fantasia
as a new member today.

455
00:35:06,938 --> 00:35:08,731
He's Director Ji Kang-woo.

456
00:35:18,658 --> 00:35:19,992
I will let this one slide today.

457
00:35:20,284 --> 00:35:22,620
I want you to stop putting
on these kinds of

458
00:35:22,703 --> 00:35:23,913
rash acts from now on.

459
00:35:24,413 --> 00:35:26,124
Well, the situation is very serious.

460
00:35:28,835 --> 00:35:31,420
What you said
about Lee Yeon-seo earlier...

461
00:35:31,879 --> 00:35:32,880
You're not serious, are you?

462
00:35:32,964 --> 00:35:33,965
No, I was serious.

463
00:35:35,758 --> 00:35:36,968
Let me make myself very clear.

464
00:35:37,051 --> 00:35:40,346
I, Choi Yeong-ja, am the one
who hired you, Director Ji.

465
00:35:40,471 --> 00:35:41,722
Let me make myself very clear too.

466
00:35:41,848 --> 00:35:44,392
The contract dictates that I have
complete control over the program

467
00:35:45,017 --> 00:35:46,269
and the appointment of dancers.

468
00:35:46,352 --> 00:35:48,896
Only after discussing it with me.

469
00:35:49,564 --> 00:35:50,648
That will be impossible.

470
00:35:50,731 --> 00:35:53,192
If ballerinas rest for a day,
they feel the effect.

471
00:35:53,442 --> 00:35:54,986
If they rest for two,
their partners feel it.

472
00:35:55,069 --> 00:35:57,071
And if they rest for four days,
the audience will see it.

473
00:35:58,072 --> 00:35:59,657
Yeon-seo hasn't danced for three years.

474
00:35:59,740 --> 00:36:02,243
She can't do a fouettÃ©
because she can see now.

475
00:36:02,535 --> 00:36:03,786
I was going to make her do it

476
00:36:04,537 --> 00:36:05,955
even when she was blind.

477
00:36:06,038 --> 00:36:07,498
As long as she agrees,

478
00:36:07,582 --> 00:36:09,458
it won't take long
for her to get in shape.

479
00:36:09,542 --> 00:36:11,752
She's truly a talented dancer,

480
00:36:11,836 --> 00:36:13,421
so help me persuade her.

481
00:36:14,797 --> 00:36:15,840
Her aunt

482
00:36:16,757 --> 00:36:17,884
and her cousin

483
00:36:19,093 --> 00:36:20,511
should do so with all of their hearts.

484
00:36:25,099 --> 00:36:26,017
I knew it.

485
00:36:26,434 --> 00:36:28,060
You don't want to do it
because your sister

486
00:36:28,477 --> 00:36:29,395
will lose her spot.

487
00:36:29,729 --> 00:36:31,689
No. I've made my decision

488
00:36:31,772 --> 00:36:33,441
as the Associate Director of Fantasia.

489
00:36:33,733 --> 00:36:35,902
I like your ambition,
but that won't happen.

490
00:36:35,985 --> 00:36:38,821
If the prima ballerina's position becomes
vacant after overhauling our schedule,

491
00:36:38,905 --> 00:36:39,947
we'll be a laughingstock.

492
00:36:40,031 --> 00:36:43,659
And you will rightly be held
responsible for it.

493
00:36:45,036 --> 00:36:46,037
I understand.

494
00:36:47,496 --> 00:36:48,623
I'll do it myself.

495
00:36:49,081 --> 00:36:51,584
Yeon-seo isn't easily persuaded.

496
00:36:51,959 --> 00:36:53,127
It's no fun if she is.

497
00:37:02,595 --> 00:37:03,804
BAEGUN-DONG
IVY MANSION

498
00:37:13,397 --> 00:37:14,690
You're here for an interview, right?

499
00:37:15,483 --> 00:37:17,401
Yes. I think so.

500
00:37:17,735 --> 00:37:19,570
-Don't breathe loudly.
-What?

501
00:37:19,904 --> 00:37:22,573
I just got fired for breathing too loudly.

502
00:37:26,118 --> 00:37:27,536
She's so picky.

503
00:37:28,788 --> 00:37:30,373
Hey, are you all right?

504
00:37:30,456 --> 00:37:32,458
Yes, I am. Thank you. Goodbye.

505
00:37:32,541 --> 00:37:34,543
-Thank you.
-Sure.

506
00:37:37,797 --> 00:37:38,965
Thank you for your time.

507
00:37:52,895 --> 00:37:55,022
You fired 20 people within 3 hours.

508
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:56,482
You're impressive indeed.

509
00:37:56,565 --> 00:37:58,317
You know that wasting time
isn't how I roll.

510
00:37:58,401 --> 00:37:59,735
You should at least test them.

511
00:37:59,819 --> 00:38:01,737
You should try holding
their arms and stand up.

512
00:38:01,821 --> 00:38:03,281
Can't you tell that they're all duds?

513
00:38:04,490 --> 00:38:05,992
No matter how much they resemble him,

514
00:38:06,909 --> 00:38:08,619
no one can be him.

515
00:38:08,786 --> 00:38:09,996
The doctor said

516
00:38:10,204 --> 00:38:12,832
that it might be better
if they had a similar vibe.

517
00:38:13,708 --> 00:38:17,086
Some people use teddy bears
to replace the deceased.

518
00:38:18,671 --> 00:38:20,339
Instead of fake teddy bears,

519
00:38:20,506 --> 00:38:22,508
I'd rather have a rude butler like you.

520
00:38:23,843 --> 00:38:25,386
-You're holding a grudge.
-Grudge? If I was,

521
00:38:25,469 --> 00:38:26,804
I would've made you write an apology.

522
00:38:26,887 --> 00:38:28,472
If you keep doing this,
you can't hire anyone.

523
00:38:28,556 --> 00:38:30,766
Let's just hire a driver
and a secretary from the current staff.

524
00:38:30,850 --> 00:38:31,976
No one applied for the position.

525
00:38:32,059 --> 00:38:34,061
Even with the 200-percent bonus,
no one applied.

526
00:38:34,145 --> 00:38:36,105
This is all thanks to
that temper of yours.

527
00:38:37,982 --> 00:38:39,108
Then, keep looking.

528
00:38:39,191 --> 00:38:41,527
You told me not to waste these eyes.

529
00:38:58,627 --> 00:39:01,088
Hello. I'm Kim Dan, the interviewee.

530
00:39:01,339 --> 00:39:03,299
We just finished with
the last interviewee.

531
00:39:04,258 --> 00:39:05,509
I was told

532
00:39:05,593 --> 00:39:07,011
to be at Ivy Mansion by 3 p.m.

533
00:39:10,890 --> 00:39:12,016
KIM DAN

534
00:39:12,099 --> 00:39:14,518
You're right. I do have your resume.

535
00:39:16,937 --> 00:39:18,189
Mr. Kim Dan?

536
00:39:19,273 --> 00:39:20,983
How could a man in his twenties be here?

537
00:39:27,865 --> 00:39:29,033
Who was that guy?

538
00:39:29,116 --> 00:39:30,534
That was upsetting.

539
00:39:36,082 --> 00:39:37,792
Would you like to say anything
before we finish?

540
00:39:37,875 --> 00:39:39,960
Please hire me.

541
00:39:42,004 --> 00:39:43,130
I like your enthusiasm.

542
00:39:43,631 --> 00:39:45,591
I'll assist her as best I can...

543
00:39:50,179 --> 00:39:52,098
so that she could shine brightly.

