00:39:53,974 --> 00:39:55,893
I want to see you smile

545
00:39:56,685 --> 00:39:57,561
and shine brightly

546
00:39:58,145 --> 00:39:59,605
like you did then

547
00:40:00,022 --> 00:40:01,315
just one more time.

548
00:40:07,071 --> 00:40:08,697
What did you just say?

549
00:40:09,740 --> 00:40:12,785
Please. Please be effective.

550
00:40:15,287 --> 00:40:16,455
Shine brightly.

551
00:40:23,087 --> 00:40:24,171
Shine brightly.

552
00:40:24,839 --> 00:40:26,090
You'll shine brightly and sparkle.

553
00:40:26,173 --> 00:40:27,174
Stop.

554
00:40:32,346 --> 00:40:33,639
That's enough. Leave.

555
00:40:36,684 --> 00:40:38,185
Did I do something wrong?

556
00:40:38,269 --> 00:40:39,937
If you tell me what I did--

557
00:40:40,020 --> 00:40:41,522
Your interview is over, so leave.

558
00:40:42,815 --> 00:40:44,775
I have no place to go
if I don't get this job.

559
00:40:44,984 --> 00:40:46,110
My father kicked me out.

560
00:40:46,193 --> 00:40:47,987
And my uncle won't even help me.

561
00:40:48,112 --> 00:40:50,156
I'm all alone in this harsh world.

562
00:40:51,031 --> 00:40:51,949
So what?

563
00:40:55,286 --> 00:40:57,538
I was hoping you could help me.

564
00:41:15,222 --> 00:41:18,058
I thought she would be dejected,
but she's still cranky.

565
00:41:18,476 --> 00:41:20,436
They say you can't fix humans.

566
00:41:20,519 --> 00:41:21,979
Gosh, that temper of hers.

567
00:41:22,771 --> 00:41:23,772
Excuse me.

568
00:41:28,986 --> 00:41:30,362
I just said that out loud, didn't I?

569
00:41:34,867 --> 00:41:36,076
I totally forgot for a second.

570
00:41:38,954 --> 00:41:41,123
Since you already heard it,
I'll say one more thing.

571
00:41:42,082 --> 00:41:44,210
Be nice, okay?

572
00:41:44,835 --> 00:41:46,629
Be shiny. Be nice!

573
00:41:53,844 --> 00:41:54,678
What was that about?

574
00:41:57,223 --> 00:41:59,808
Hey! Stop right there!

575
00:42:00,518 --> 00:42:01,519
Ms. Lee!

576
00:42:03,270 --> 00:42:04,104
You just

577
00:42:05,064 --> 00:42:06,357
walked on your own, right?

578
00:42:16,825 --> 00:42:18,118
Gosh, I'm in trouble now!

579
00:42:18,202 --> 00:42:19,912
This is crazy. I guess
I really am a human now!

580
00:42:20,246 --> 00:42:21,914
Should I go back and apologize?

581
00:42:21,997 --> 00:42:22,915
But I don't want to.

582
00:42:22,998 --> 00:42:24,875
Then I'll dissipate.
Gosh! I don't want that.

583
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:26,001
Yes.

584
00:42:26,252 --> 00:42:27,628
I should go back, apologize to her,

585
00:42:27,962 --> 00:42:28,963
and go to paradise.

586
00:42:29,838 --> 00:42:31,840
Gosh! I don't think I can do this.

587
00:42:31,924 --> 00:42:33,175
-What do I do?
-Mr. Kim Dan!

588
00:42:33,259 --> 00:42:34,885
What should I do? I'm so torn!

589
00:42:41,976 --> 00:42:42,977
All right.

590
00:42:44,228 --> 00:42:46,480
Use this phone while on duty.
And put this next to your bed.

591
00:42:46,564 --> 00:42:48,274
Whenever it rings,
you must run to Ms. Lee.

592
00:42:48,482 --> 00:42:51,235
This is an alarm for when she's going out.
When it rings, run to where she is.

593
00:42:51,318 --> 00:42:53,654
This is her baby journal
and this is a record of her ballet career.

594
00:42:53,737 --> 00:42:55,155
This is a list of things that she hates,

595
00:42:55,239 --> 00:42:56,949
and this is for the corneal transplant.

596
00:42:57,032 --> 00:42:58,367
And most importantly,

597
00:42:59,034 --> 00:43:00,286
here's your contract.

598
00:43:04,456 --> 00:43:06,208
I have to go through all of these things?

599
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:07,418
Yes.

600
00:43:07,835 --> 00:43:08,836
By the way,

601
00:43:09,503 --> 00:43:10,462
where's your stuff?

602
00:43:11,171 --> 00:43:12,256
Is this it?

603
00:43:14,174 --> 00:43:16,093
You must be a terrible son.

604
00:43:16,176 --> 00:43:18,012
I guess you got kicked out empty-handed.

605
00:43:21,098 --> 00:43:22,683
I will return home eventually.

606
00:43:25,019 --> 00:43:26,020
Well, then.

607
00:43:26,228 --> 00:43:27,896
Thanks to you, I can call it a day.

608
00:43:28,063 --> 00:43:29,064
Take it easy.

609
00:43:46,498 --> 00:43:47,958
I got closer to her.

610
00:44:00,346 --> 00:44:02,514
Mr. Kim Dan is all moved in now.

611
00:44:04,475 --> 00:44:05,309
You may leave, then.

612
00:44:11,357 --> 00:44:13,567
The exact opposite of Mr. Cho
could be better

613
00:44:14,151 --> 00:44:16,195
than someone who is sort of
but not quite like him.

614
00:44:16,278 --> 00:44:17,363
I don't believe it.

615
00:44:18,072 --> 00:44:20,407
The spiel about the teddy bear and so on.

616
00:44:21,075 --> 00:44:23,744
-I don't believe it.
-But earlier, you took--

617
00:44:23,827 --> 00:44:25,204
That was it though.

618
00:44:26,246 --> 00:44:27,790
It's all in my mind anyway,

619
00:44:28,082 --> 00:44:29,500
so I should just overcome it.

620
00:44:31,126 --> 00:44:33,003
I will do it on my own.

621
00:44:33,587 --> 00:44:34,588
Then

622
00:44:35,547 --> 00:44:37,883
why did you hire Mr. Kim?

623
00:44:48,560 --> 00:44:49,561
LOVE

624
00:44:54,691 --> 00:44:56,110
What...

625
00:44:56,402 --> 00:44:57,569
What's this sound?

626
00:44:57,694 --> 00:44:59,405
Gosh! Where's it coming from?

627
00:45:12,960 --> 00:45:14,002
What can I do for you?

628
00:45:14,086 --> 00:45:14,920
You're too slow.

629
00:45:15,003 --> 00:45:17,131
You must show up within a minute.

630
00:45:26,515 --> 00:45:28,142
Is it not the right side?

631
00:45:28,517 --> 00:45:29,643
I read that you always stand

632
00:45:29,726 --> 00:45:32,062
on the right side,
so I should offer my left arm.

633
00:45:34,356 --> 00:45:36,024
Gosh, don't.

634
00:45:36,692 --> 00:45:38,193
Come on.

635
00:45:38,735 --> 00:45:40,320
Here, hold my arm.

636
00:45:56,462 --> 00:45:58,464
Oh, look at you! You're walking!

637
00:46:02,718 --> 00:46:04,303
You don't need to thank me.

638
00:46:04,470 --> 00:46:07,055
Since this already happened,
you should try to recover quickly.

639
00:46:07,139 --> 00:46:08,557
Then you'll feel better,

640
00:46:08,640 --> 00:46:10,642
and with the gentle spring breeze--

641
00:46:10,726 --> 00:46:11,727
Be quiet.

642
00:46:13,562 --> 00:46:14,813
I hate the noise.

643
00:46:16,106 --> 00:46:17,107
Just walk.

644
00:46:20,152 --> 00:46:21,361
Where are you going?

645
00:46:35,459 --> 00:46:36,460
You're so bad at this.

646
00:46:36,543 --> 00:46:38,337
Why does a secretary
have to learn to do this?

647
00:46:38,420 --> 00:46:39,671
Please teach him well.

648
00:46:39,755 --> 00:46:42,174
His bones will break
if he and I have a match.

649
00:46:43,217 --> 00:46:44,343
Teach him the pinning technique.

650
00:46:49,139 --> 00:46:51,058
Tap!

651
00:46:52,100 --> 00:46:53,101
I'm doomed.

652
00:46:53,185 --> 00:46:56,730
There isn't a single ounce of love
in this woman.

653
00:47:05,322 --> 00:47:06,323
Get out.

654
00:47:09,618 --> 00:47:10,744
The corridor!

655
00:47:16,667 --> 00:47:18,335
You call this cleaning?

656
00:47:18,585 --> 00:47:21,296
Do better. Clean properly!

657
00:47:22,214 --> 00:47:24,091
Were human beings really made

658
00:47:24,383 --> 00:47:26,635
into the reflection of the deity?

659
00:47:31,515 --> 00:47:33,100
You can't even add up
the calories correctly?

660
00:47:34,768 --> 00:47:35,686
I won't eat this.

661
00:47:35,769 --> 00:47:38,438
Then why is she so condescending

662
00:47:38,647 --> 00:47:40,357
and rude?

663
00:47:43,819 --> 00:47:45,529
Mr, they smell amazing.
Smell these flowers.

664
00:47:50,826 --> 00:47:52,286
She doesn't know how to be impressed,

665
00:47:52,369 --> 00:47:54,121
and she's incapable of being marveled.

666
00:47:54,204 --> 00:47:56,873
There are 198 things
on her list of things she hates.

667
00:47:57,874 --> 00:48:00,919
No one in this mansion loves her.

668
00:48:02,421 --> 00:48:03,422
That includes me.

669
00:48:06,758 --> 00:48:08,218
But wait and see.

670
00:48:08,635 --> 00:48:10,345
No matter what happens,

671
00:48:11,638 --> 00:48:12,639
I will make

672
00:48:13,307 --> 00:48:14,808
you learn to love.

673
00:49:14,868 --> 00:49:18,163
As you know,
when I was the only principal dancer here,

674
00:49:18,246 --> 00:49:20,123
Keum Ni-na was my understudy.

675
00:49:20,582 --> 00:49:22,209
In other words, she was my shadow.

676
00:49:23,251 --> 00:49:24,878
You're 16th note faster.

677
00:49:26,421 --> 00:49:28,507
If you die, get sad,

678
00:49:28,590 --> 00:49:30,676
and fall in love before the music,

679
00:49:31,468 --> 00:49:33,303
it's rushed and kills the expectations.

680
00:49:43,188 --> 00:49:44,940
I thought being rushed
was your only problem,

681
00:49:45,023 --> 00:49:46,233
but you're actually dumb.

682
00:50:00,664 --> 00:50:01,873
Do you want to break your ankle?

683
00:50:02,374 --> 00:50:05,210
You know what "next time" means
to ballerinas.

684
00:50:06,336 --> 00:50:08,672
"I don't want to see your dance, ever.
You won't make it."

685
00:50:09,715 --> 00:50:12,634
You don't want to give me another chance.

686
00:50:14,386 --> 00:50:15,846
You've already made your decision.

687
00:50:17,681 --> 00:50:19,433
When I say, "next time", I keep my word.

688
00:50:19,516 --> 00:50:20,600
I don't sugarcoat things.

689
00:50:46,877 --> 00:50:47,878
I'm back.

690
00:50:58,013 --> 00:50:59,556
PRINCIPAL DANCER
OF FANTASIA BALLET THEATER

691
00:50:59,639 --> 00:51:00,974
KEUM KI-CHUN, CHOI YEONG-JA, MARRIED

692
00:51:01,057 --> 00:51:02,476
KEUM RU-NA, ASSOCIATE DIRECTOR

693
00:51:03,477 --> 00:51:05,771
KEUM NI-NA, PRINCIPAL DANCER

694
00:51:08,023 --> 00:51:10,650
LEE YEON-SEO, REGAINED HER EYESIGHT

695
00:51:16,782 --> 00:51:17,783
How's she doing?

696
00:51:18,408 --> 00:51:19,618
She still can't walk?

697
00:51:21,536 --> 00:51:23,079
She can move around now

698
00:51:23,246 --> 00:51:24,706
after she hired a new secretary?

699
00:51:32,506 --> 00:51:33,673
Then should I

700
00:51:34,674 --> 00:51:35,801
get started now?

701
00:51:42,057 --> 00:51:43,809
Don't worry about it.

702
00:51:44,434 --> 00:51:46,394
Yeon-seo just got surgery.

703
00:51:46,937 --> 00:51:48,688
And she took three years off.

704
00:51:48,772 --> 00:51:50,482
It won't be easy for her to return.

705
00:51:51,107 --> 00:51:52,359
That surgery!

706
00:51:54,402 --> 00:51:57,989
How did you manage it so that she could
receive corneas after a car accident?

707
00:51:58,698 --> 00:52:00,742
I had no idea that Mr. Cho designated her

708
00:52:00,826 --> 00:52:02,035
as the receiver.

709
00:52:02,452 --> 00:52:05,956
You know that I tried to stop her
from receiving it

710
00:52:06,039 --> 00:52:07,332
whenever there was one available.

711
00:52:07,415 --> 00:52:08,750
The biter is bitten.

712
00:52:09,793 --> 00:52:10,919
My gosh.

713
00:52:11,086 --> 00:52:12,629
The minister is also giving me pressure

714
00:52:12,712 --> 00:52:14,089
with her regaining eyesight.

715
00:52:14,548 --> 00:52:17,092
I mean, what if she asks
for the foundation

716
00:52:17,843 --> 00:52:19,803
because she can see now?

717
00:52:20,053 --> 00:52:21,972
We should give it back.
It was originally hers.

718
00:52:24,808 --> 00:52:26,268
You idiot.

719
00:52:26,768 --> 00:52:28,895
You can go back to that life of debt

720
00:52:28,979 --> 00:52:31,773
and suffer from having to
walk on eggshells around others.

721
00:52:32,107 --> 00:52:33,525
But as for me,

722
00:52:33,900 --> 00:52:35,402
I am not going back to that life.

723
00:52:41,825 --> 00:52:42,909
Did you check?

724
00:52:44,870 --> 00:52:46,621
I'm sure you'll find something.

725
00:52:47,747 --> 00:52:48,748
What?

726
00:52:49,624 --> 00:52:51,835
His things are still there?

727
00:52:58,800 --> 00:53:01,553
Then we should clean it out for her.

728
00:53:04,556 --> 00:53:06,725
Hey!

729
00:53:14,441 --> 00:53:15,775
Who's in charge of the garden today?

730
00:53:17,152 --> 00:53:19,112
I just stepped on wet petals, slipped,

731
00:53:19,195 --> 00:53:21,031
and almost cracked my head open.

732
00:53:21,114 --> 00:53:22,073
Who was in charge?

733
00:53:25,118 --> 00:53:26,995
-You should stop.
-Don't get into this.

734
00:53:27,078 --> 00:53:28,538
I'll clean up the garden.

735
00:53:28,622 --> 00:53:30,665
I'll pick up every single petal left here.

736
00:53:30,749 --> 00:53:31,666
Happy?

737
00:53:33,668 --> 00:53:35,170
You can go back.

738
00:53:36,671 --> 00:53:37,923
Do not go back.

739
00:53:43,428 --> 00:53:44,721
This is beyond your power.

740
00:53:44,804 --> 00:53:46,473
Do you want me to read over the contract?

741
00:53:46,556 --> 00:53:48,433
I haven't signed it yet anyway.

742
00:53:48,516 --> 00:53:50,143
While we're on it,
should we look into the laws

743
00:53:50,226 --> 00:53:51,603
on the overuse of power by an employer?

744
00:53:51,686 --> 00:53:53,730
I'll go into every single detail on that.

745
00:53:55,190 --> 00:53:57,567
Go back inside. Come on, go back.

746
00:53:58,902 --> 00:54:00,070
Yes, go.

747
00:54:02,030 --> 00:54:03,031
You!

748
00:54:07,369 --> 00:54:08,495
You hate the sunset, don't you?

749
00:54:09,704 --> 00:54:11,915
-What?
-You always throw a fit during the sunset.

750
00:54:12,165 --> 00:54:14,626
What is it? Were you dumped at sunset?

751
00:54:14,876 --> 00:54:17,879
Did you see your first love
having an affair under the red sky?

752
00:54:17,963 --> 00:54:19,047
What is it?

753
00:54:19,130 --> 00:54:21,800
Yes, the sunset always drives me crazy.

754
00:54:22,092 --> 00:54:23,635
I want to burn anyone that I see

755
00:54:23,718 --> 00:54:25,136
with the burning sun.

756
00:54:25,220 --> 00:54:26,221
Happy now?

757
00:54:27,889 --> 00:54:29,307
If you know better, why do you do that?

758
00:54:29,391 --> 00:54:32,602
They say you get over someone
you've loved with someone new.

759
00:54:33,603 --> 00:54:34,938
Why don't you meet someone great

760
00:54:35,981 --> 00:54:37,607
before you go crazier?

761
00:54:39,234 --> 00:54:40,568
There is this saying too.

762
00:54:40,860 --> 00:54:42,612
"Even if we speak
with the tongues of angels,

763
00:54:42,696 --> 00:54:43,989
even if we gain all the world
and its knowledge,

764
00:54:44,072 --> 00:54:45,740
even if we sacrifice ourselves,

765
00:54:45,824 --> 00:54:46,950
without love,

766
00:54:47,659 --> 00:54:48,827
we have nothing."

767
00:54:51,538 --> 00:54:52,580
Come to think of it, I regret

768
00:54:53,498 --> 00:54:55,250
I didn't ask about your religion
in the interview.

769
00:54:57,210 --> 00:54:58,837
Make sure this place is spotless.

770
00:55:25,905 --> 00:55:27,490
Excuse me. I'll take this one.

771
00:55:44,299 --> 00:55:45,759
"Tongues of angels"?

772
00:55:48,636 --> 00:55:50,180
That phony religious jerk.

773
00:55:50,764 --> 00:55:52,348
You're neither a pervert nor a pickpocket.

774
00:55:52,766 --> 00:55:53,975
You're from some religious cult?

775
00:55:54,059 --> 00:55:55,685
Not everyone behaves like you

776
00:55:55,769 --> 00:55:57,353
after experiencing a tragedy.

777
00:55:59,105 --> 00:56:00,190
Could it be?

778
00:56:13,620 --> 00:56:16,247
This rain is exactly like Lee Yeon-seo.

779
00:56:16,331 --> 00:56:19,417
No matter how much I sweep,
this rain is making more petals fall down.

780
00:56:19,751 --> 00:56:21,586
In a word, it's useless.

781
00:56:21,669 --> 00:56:22,921
It's all in vain.

782
00:56:23,922 --> 00:56:24,923
I mean,

783
00:56:25,924 --> 00:56:27,342
she has nothing I can work with.

784
00:56:28,009 --> 00:56:30,345
If she likes something,
I can start with that.

785
00:56:31,638 --> 00:56:33,139
Her soul is like Sodom and Gomorrah.

786
00:56:52,700 --> 00:56:54,035
What? Why are these out?

787
00:56:55,078 --> 00:56:56,246
What is this?

788
00:56:57,956 --> 00:56:59,124
What's going on?

789
00:57:00,291 --> 00:57:01,334
What is this?

790
00:57:05,672 --> 00:57:06,714
Gosh.

791
00:57:07,006 --> 00:57:08,424
NOISY GONG

792
00:57:08,675 --> 00:57:09,926
Darn it.

793
00:57:11,803 --> 00:57:13,888
KIM DAN

794
00:57:41,624 --> 00:57:42,876
She's gone.

795
00:58:20,914 --> 00:58:22,207
Gosh, darn it.

796
00:58:23,291 --> 00:58:25,877
Dismissed. Begone.

797
00:58:26,169 --> 00:58:28,171
My gosh, this is driving me crazy.

798
00:58:28,463 --> 00:58:31,925
This is an emergency. I need this fixed.
This body is malfunctioning.

799
00:58:32,008 --> 00:58:33,384
My gosh. Seriously.

800
00:58:43,478 --> 00:58:44,729
Lee Yeon-seo.

801
00:58:45,021 --> 00:58:46,940
Oh, gosh, no.

802
00:59:04,123 --> 00:59:05,291
My goodness.

803
00:59:17,303 --> 00:59:18,555
No, please. No.

804
01:02:09,726 --> 01:02:10,643
Humans...

805
01:02:11,394 --> 01:02:13,187
I especially have no idea
what Lee Yeon-seo is like.

806
01:02:13,354 --> 01:02:14,272
Now, one, two, three.

807
01:02:14,355 --> 01:02:15,440
Hey, that hurts.

808
01:02:15,523 --> 01:02:16,566
He's a pervert and a lunatic.

809
01:02:16,649 --> 01:02:19,318
I don't know if she ever liked anyone
or if there is someone

810
01:02:19,402 --> 01:02:21,154
who makes her happy just
with the thought of them.

811
01:02:21,571 --> 01:02:24,240
I actually want to see it badly too.

812
01:02:24,407 --> 01:02:27,618
What should I do to make
